ca_breweries <- "https://www.ratebeer.com/breweries/unitedstates/5/213/"
nc_breweries <- "https://www.ratebeer.com/breweries/unitedstates/33/213/"
scrape_url <- function(x) {
  urls <- x %>%
    read_html() %>%
    html_nodes(".inactive a") %>%
    html_attr("href") %>%
    paste("https://www.ratebeer.com", .,sep = "")
  
  for (i in 1:3) {
  
  producer_name <-
    read_html(urls[i]) %>%
    html_nodes("#brewerTable a:nth-child(1)") %>%
    html_text() 
    
  
  if (length(producer_name) == 0) { 
   urls <- urls[-i]
  } 
  
  }

   return(urls)
}
ca_urls <- scrape_url(ca_breweries)

nc_urls <- scrape_url(nc_breweries)

Explanation: First I created vectors to save the urls for CA (my state of choice and the state I wanted to test the function on first) and NC (the state required by Professor Ballenger). From here, I created a function that would scrape the 3 urls of the meadery, cidery, and sake producer pages for each state. I used web scraping functions like read_html, html_nodes, and html_attr (to specify I wanted links) to indicate the selector/html element needed to tell the function what information I wanted scraped (the urls of each alcohol type). From here, I used paste so that the entire url (including the beginning) would be displayed after scraping.

After this, I made a loop that would feed each url through it and detect whether or not each alcohol type actually had any producers. Theres an if statement there that tells the program to delete the url of an alcohol type from the output if that alcohol type doesnt have producers to speak of.

After I set up my function, I tested it on the NC and CA vectors I made before making the function and assigned the results to new vectors as requested.

Question 2

scrape_beverage_producer_data <- function(x) {
  y <- read_html(x)
  producer_name <- y %>%
    html_nodes("#brewerTable a:nth-child(1)") %>%
    html_text()
  
  active_producer_city <- y %>%
    html_nodes(".filter") %>%
    html_text() 
  
  closed_producer_city <- y %>%
    html_nodes("#brewerTable span") %>%
    html_text() 
    
  producer_city <- c(active_producer_city, closed_producer_city)
  
  producer_type <- y %>%
    html_nodes("td.hidden-sm") %>%
    html_text()
  
  producer_established <- y %>%
    html_nodes("td:nth-child(5)") %>%
    html_text() %>%
    as.numeric()
  
  producer_number_of_beverages <- y %>%
    html_nodes(".hidden-sm+ td") %>%
    html_text() %>%
    str_trim() %>%
    as.numeric()  
  
  status_active <- rep("Active", length(active_producer_city))
  
  status_closed <- rep("Closed", length(closed_producer_city))
  
  status <- c(status_active, status_closed)
  
  producer_data <- tibble(
    name = producer_name,
    city = producer_city,
    type = producer_type,
    year_established = producer_established,
    beverage_count = producer_number_of_beverages,
    status = status
  )
  
  return(producer_data)
}
